'''Jos<U+00E9> Luis L<U+00F3>pez Panizo''' (born [[Sestao]], [[Vizcaya]], [[January 12]] [[1922]]), usually shortened to '''Panizo''', was a [[Football in Spain|Spanish]]/[[Basque people|Basque]] footballer who played for  [[Athletic de Bilbao]], [[SD Indautxu]] and [[Spain national football team|Spain]] during the 1940s and 1950s. Panizo first played for Nuevo Porto Arsenal and then joined [[Sestao Sport Club]] for the 1938/39 season. He made his debut for [[Athletic de Bilbao]] during the 1939/40 season. He was a member of the Atl<U+00E9>tico team that won the [[La Liga]]/[[Copa del Generalisimo|Copa]] double in 1942/43 and the  [[Copa del Generalisimo]] three times in a row between 1943 and 1945. He played 405 games for Atl<U+00E9>tico including 326 in [[La Liga]] and scored 126 league goals in sixteen seasons. Panizo made his debut for [[Spain national football team|Spain]] in 1946 and subsequently played 14 games, scoring twice. He was a member of the [[Spain national football team|Spanish]] squad during the [[1950 FIFA World Cup]]. He finished his playing career at [[SD Indautxu]]   

==Honours==
* '''[[La Liga|Spanish Champions]]: 1'''
** 1942-43  
* ''' [[Copa del Generalisimo]]: 4''' 
** 1943, 1944, 1945, 1950

